class="main_column"><h1>Welcome to BMC Associates</h1><p>BMC Associates helps business partners, owners of family businesses, and principals of other organizations deal with conflict and build collaboration. BMC&#8217;s interdisciplinary and non-adversarial approach helps strengthen working teams&#8217; overall business and interpersonal performance.<script type="text/javascript" src="//platform.linkedin.com/in.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" data-id="2460879" data-counter="none"></script></p><p>BMC&#8217;s services include:</p><ul><li><strong><a
title="Mediation" href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/resolve-conflict/mediation/">Mediation</a></strong>, a process that resolves conflicts through facilitated negotiations.</li><li><strong><a
title="Partnership Charter" href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/prevent-conflict/partnership-charter/">The Partnership Charter</a></strong>, an innovative, preventative tool for partners and partners-to-be who want a structured approach to negotiating the many issues that tend to cause difficulties and conflicts among partners.</li><li><strong><a
title="Succession Planning" href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/prevent-conflict/succession-planning/">Business Succession Plans</a></strong>, an integrated approach to transferring family business leadership and ownership.</li><li><strong><a
title="Collaborative Estate Planning" href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/prevent-conflict/collaborative-estate-planning/">Collaborative Estate Planning</a></strong>, a way for families to address the many sensitive issues involved in transferring assets such as vacation properties from one generation to the next.</li><li><strong><a
title="Strengthen Relationships" href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/strengthen-relationships/">Other Services</a></strong> that meet the planning and organizational development needs of clients are offered in conjunction with the services described above.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Recent News &amp; Updates</h3><div
class="recent_news"><h4><a
href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/other-news/mpa-workshop/">MPA Workshop</a></h4>October 28, 2018<p><strong>Event</strong>: Maryland Psychological Association Annual Convention</p><p><strong>Event Date</strong>: November 2, 2018</p><p><strong>Location</strong>: Baltimore, Maryland</p><p>The Maryland Psychological Association asked Drs. Donna and David Gage to present a workshop at their Annual Convention about the many ways psychologists can use mediation to help their clients. They will focus on mediation with business partners, boards of directors, management teams and families with business and estate issues, but they will emphasize how psychologists’ training and experience make them particularly well suited to work in any conflict situations that involve close relationships.</p><h4><a
href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/other-news/continuing-education-program/">Continuing Education Program</a></h4>October 15, 2017<p><strong>Event</strong>: DC Psychological Association</p><p><strong>Event Date</strong>: October 20, 2017</p><p><strong>Location</strong>: Washington, DC</p><p>David and Donna Gage gave a workshop for psychologists, social workers and executive coaches on how BMC uses a multidisciplinary approach to help family business owners resolve complex family and business conflicts collaboratively.</p><h4><a
href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/other-news/presentation_annual_convention/">Presentation at Annual Convention</a></h4>April 21, 2017<p><strong>Event</strong>: American Psychological Association’s Annual Conference</p><p><strong>Event Date</strong>: August 6, 2017</p><p><strong>Location</strong>: Washington, DC</p><p>Dr. David Gage presented a talk entitled “Siblings in Conflict: Tied at the Hip in the Family Business” at the world’s largest annual conference of psychologists. He talked to psychologists from around the world about how siblings jointly inherit family assets and suddenly find themselves not just siblings, but also business partners.</p><h4><a
href="http://www.bmcassociates.com/other-news/apa_april_webinar/">Dr. Gage Interviewed For APA Webinar</a></h4>April 20, 2017<p><strong>Event</strong>: American Psychological Association Webinar</p><p><strong>Event Date</strong>: April 25, 2017</p><p>Dr. David Gage was interviewed on the American Psychological Association’s on-going webinar series, “How Did You Get That Job?”  The series explores how the knowledge, skills, and experience gained through psychologists&#8217; education and training can successfully transfer to a variety of jobs that they may never have considered.</p><h5>Other News &amp; Updates</h5><span
